Package p4_group_8_repo

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ButtonGenerator
    Helps in generating buttons for a game scene/screen
    ImageGenerator
    Helps in generating images for the game objects Actor
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Actor
    Actor Class is the base class for all the interactive objects in the Frogger Game.
    Each interactive game object is known as an Actor.
    Animal
    Animal is the player's Avatar in the game, which in this case is the Frog.
    BackgroundImage
    Represents the background images for the game.
    Used for each game level, StartScreen, InfoScreen and High Score Pop Up.
    Digit
    Represents the game points of the Animal
    End
    Represents the destination the Animal should reach to win the game.
    There are three types of End : an empty End, an activated End with a coin for bonus game points, an End that has been reached by the Animal.
    HighScoreComparator  
    HighScoreController
    HighScoreController can retrieve HighScoreModel information, record the information into file in descending order and update to HighScoreView.
    HighScoreModel
    Player's high score record.
    HighScoreView
    Represents how high score pop up will look like in the game.
    InfoScreen
    Represents the Information Screen of the game.
    Singleton Design Pattern is applied to this class, so there is only 1 InfoScreen instance throughout the game.
    Level1
    Level 1 of the Frogger Game.
    Level2
    Level 2 of the Frogger Game.
    Level3  
    Level4  
    Level5  
    LevelFactory
    This is a Level Factory to retrieve the game levels.
    LevelMaster
    The base class for all game levels.
    Template Design Pattern is applied, where LevelMaster class has abstract methods to be implemented differently by its subclasses.
    Log
    Represents the Logs in Frogger Game
    Main  
    Monster  
    Obstacle  
    StartScreen  
    Turtle  
    WetTurtle  
    World
